cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LT, cs.CC, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with denotational semantics and equational/order theories of lambda calculus, which are closely related to logic.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as lambda calculus is a fundamental concept in programming languages and the paper discusses lambda-models and combinatory algebras.
- cs.LT (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as lambda calculus can be seen as a formal language and the paper deals with equational theories.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the effectiveness of lambda-models.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also less likely but possible as lambda calculus has applications in information theory and the paper deals with mathematical representations of lambda calculus.
